 Anthony Martial and Scott McTominay scored for Manchester United to secure  a 2-0 victory over rivals Manchester City on Sunday. This is the first time since the departure of Sir Alex Ferguson that the Red Devils will be recording a double victory over Man. City in a Premier League season. The Red Devils currently sit fifth in the Premier League table, three points behind Chelsea, who massacred Everton 4-0 earlier in Stamford Bridge.   Details Shortly…………….